Package ex0

Class Graph_DS

java.lang.Object
ex0.Graph_DS
All Implemented Interfaces:
graph
public class Graph_DS
extends java.lang.Object
implements graph
This class represents an undirected unweighted graph. The implementation based on adjacency list representation - created with HashMap data structure for accessing vertices quickly. The class implements the interface graph - for more documentation visit this interface.

  • Constructor Details

    • Graph_DS

      public Graph_DS()

    • Graph_DS

      public Graph_DS​(graph other)
      Creates a new graph that is a deep copy of a given other graph. The constructor copy each node of the other graph to the new graph and than seek for any possible edge in the other graph and connect the parallel nodes in the new graph. The method runs in O(n^2) time.
      Parameters:
      other - graph to copy from
